                             <table width="100%" style="min-width: 100%;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tbody><tr>
<td class="editor-text editor-text " align="left" valign="top" style="font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; color: #403F42; text-align: left; display: block; word-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.2; padding: 10px 20px;"> 
                                 <div></div> 
                                 <div class="text-container galileo-ap-content-editor">
                                  <div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Dear parents and guardians.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">As many of you are aware, Mayor DiBlasio announced yesterday that New York City schools would be closed for the rest of the year. Unfortunately, this was not coordinated with the Governor’s Office and has now created more confusion.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">The City School District of New Rochelle understands that many parents are eager to find out what the remainder of this year will look like. Please know that the central administration team is working in concert with building leaders and teachers to prepare for all contingencies. Through active collaboration with the Curriculum Council, a team of professional spanning across all levels of management, and constant communication with our building principals we feel very equipped to roll out our Distance Learning Plan 2.0 in the near future.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">As further details emerge about the future of this school year, we will be ready and well poised to address the same. We are committed to ensuring that students are supported through this process. We understand that for some, the distance learning platform is not ideal. It is our responsibility as leaders of this complex district to ensure that solutions are nuanced and sensitive to the needs of all of our students.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">All aspects of a child’s education are constantly our focus. Students’ access to important curriculum in line with the states mandated standards along with their social and emotional health is always at the center of our planning. We are ready to consider many tiers of intervention and supports including a robust summer school, if needed.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Students who are excelling are also a top priority. We must ensure that the quality of the curriculum and instruction meets their ever-growing need for challenge and educational excitement.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">The City School District of New Rochelle recommends that we continue to live in the present. It is important that we focus on our families and limit sources of extraneous stress over which we have no control. The city school district’s central administration team is ready to address any of the solutions which may be presented by the Governor’s Office and New York State Education Department.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">We encourage you to enjoy the rest of your weekend and rest assured that the district will ensure that students emerge from this experience with the knowledge that they have successfully triumphed over very difficult circumstances. This is something that we will teach our children to be very proud of. We thank you as a community for your continued support. If we remain laser focused on the students, we will be successful in ensuring that our mission and goals are met.</span>
                                   </div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <br>
</div> 
                                   <div>
                                    <span style="font-size: 14px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Sincerely,</span>
